# Git Workflow

## Branch Strategy

Use feature branches off `main`. Never commit directly to `main` for feature work.

```
git switch main && git pull
git switch -c feature/<ticket-id>-<short-description>
```

Examples:
- `feature/eng-002-fraction-engine`
- `feature/eng-010-chat-panel`
- `feature/eng-020-assessment-pools`

## Commit Conventions

Use Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `test:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `style:`, `chore:`

Commit in logical increments:
1. Tests first: `test: add property-based tests for FractionEngine (ENG-003)`
2. Implementation: `feat: implement FractionEngine core operations (ENG-002)`
3. Integration: `feat: wire workspace blocks to reducer (ENG-009)`

Reference the ticket ID (ENG-XXX) from the PRD sprint plan in commit messages.

## When Done With a Feature

1. Push the feature branch: `git push -u origin feature/<ticket-id>-<short-description>`
2. Open a PR against `main`
3. Do NOT merge without review (or explicit user approval)

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT commit to `main` directly for feature work
- Do NOT force-push without explicit approval
- Do NOT commit `.env`, `node_modules/`, `.DS_Store`, or `dist/`
- Do NOT commit with failing tests
- Do NOT amend pushed commits without approval
